Interface IngestCallback<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - A generic type for ingested entries
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataStatistics<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataStatistics, AltIndexIngestCallback, BoundingBoxDataStatistics, CountDataStatistics, DataStatisticsBuilder, FeatureBoundingBoxStatistics, FeatureNumericRangeStatistics, FeatureTimeRangeStatistics, HistogramStatistics, IngestCallbackList, NumericRangeDataStatistics, OverviewStatistics, RasterBoundingBoxStatistics, RasterFootprintStatistics, StatsCompositionTool, TimeRangeDataStatistics

    public interface IngestCallback<T>
    This interface provides a callback mechanism when ingesting a collection of entries to receive the row IDs where each entry is ingested

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void entryIngested(DataStoreEntryInfo entryInfo, T entry)
      This will be called after an entry is successfully ingested with the row IDs that were used
